🖍️ Highlight App
🌟 Overview
The Highlight App is a simple and intuitive web application that allows users to search for specific text within a paragraph and highlight all occurrences of the searched term. Perfect for study sessions, research, or just casual reading, this app makes it easy to spot important information quickly.

✨ Features
🔍 Text Search: Type in any text, and the app will highlight all instances of the searched term within the paragraph.
🎨 Case-Insensitive Search: No need to worry about uppercase or lowercase—find your text no matter how it's written.
⚡ Real-Time Highlighting: Instantly see highlighted results as soon as you hit the "Search" button.
💻 Technology Stack
HTML5: 🏗️ Structuring the content.
CSS3: 🎨 Styling the user interface with a clean, modern look.
JavaScript: 🧠 Implementing the logic for text searching and highlighting.
🚀 Installation
To get the Highlight App running locally, follow these steps:

Clone the repository:
bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/highlight-app.git
Navigate to the project directory:
bash
Copy code
cd highlight-app
Open index.html in your browser:
Just open the index.html file in your web browser to start using the app.
🛠️ Usage
Enter Text to Search: 📝 Type the text you want to search for in the input field.
Click Search: 🔍 Press the "Search" button to see all matches highlighted in the paragraph.
View Results: 👀 The matched text will be highlighted, making it easy to find what you’re looking for.
📁 Code Structure
index.html: 📝 Contains the structure of the app.
style.css: 🎨 Contains the styling for the app.
script.js: 🧠 Handles the search and highlight functionality.
